After talking with Vincent Massol, decided to change interface to that it accepts something like
 
  <executable>java</executable>
  <arguments>
    <argument>-classpath</argument>
    <classpath/>
    <argument>mypackage.myclass</argument>
    <argument>myarg</argument>
  </arguments>

and

  <executable>java</executable>
  <arguments>
    <argument>-classpath</argument>
    <classpath>
      <dependency>commons-io:commons-io</dependency>
      <dependency>....</dependency>
    </classpath>
    <argument>mypackage.myclass</argument>
    <argument>myarg</argument>
  </arguments>


OR (FORMAT NOT YET CHOSEN)

 <executable>java</executable>
  <arguments>
    <argument>-classpath</argument>
    <classpath>
      <autocompute>true</autocompute>
    </classpath>
    <argument>mypackage.myclass</argument>
    <argument>myarg</argument>
  </arguments>

and 

  <executable>java</executable>
  <arguments>
    <argument>-classpath</argument>
    <classpath>
      <dependencies>
        <dependency>commons-io:commons-io</dependency>
        <dependency>....</dependency>
      </dependencies>
    </classpath>
    <argument>mypackage.myclass</argument>
    <argument>myarg</argument>
  </arguments>


with support of <dependencies> not in the first phase
